-- =============================================================================
-- Section 16: Open and closed subsets
-- =============================================================================

-- In the synthetic topology, every type X has a canonical topology where:
-- - An open subset of X is a function X Рєњ ╬Е_open (the type of open propositions)
-- - A closed subset of X is a function X Рєњ ╬Е_closed (the type of closed propositions)

